result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Donald A L Gary was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine/costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Same repayment conditions as noted above for the fine.

Defendant is entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.   Pursuant to s. 346.65(7), Wis. Stats., Defendant shall be required to remain in the County Jail for not less than a 48 consecutive hour period prior to release for huber. The Court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction.
Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt:
Case called @ 2:55 p.m. Defendant Donald A L Gary in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives right to counsel at this time and wishes to speak with the DA. Recess for the parties to talk. 
Case recalled @ 3:03 p.m. The parties have reached an agreement.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 1 - Guilty.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Ct 2 - Dismissed outright. No statement by DE. Court orders: 15 days WC Jail - Huber, GT, No CFTS - Sentence to commence by no later than 3-1-2016, the Court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction, $1442 fine inclusive of costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, $42.50 blood draw reimbursment w/ 60 DTP or PP, 13 mo DL rev/13 mo IID, OWI Assessment, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case Called @ 3:00 PM: Defendant Donald A L Gary in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel - does not have funds to hire his own counsel.  Def is currently on a short term medical disability, though is employed.  Based upon disability payments beng rec'd.  Court believes that Def will be eligible for SPD services and refers Def to SPD for eligibility.   NGP entered by the Court.   DA argues as to Signature Bond of $1500.00 w/conditions.   No statement offered by Def as to bond request.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Court dismisses 15TR-2569 and 15TR-2645 w/o prejudice.  Status conference scheduled for January 13, 2016 at 02:45 pm.
